Key Match Events: Draymond Green was initially not whistled for his sixth foul with 1:26 remaining in the fourth quarter
Pre-Game Insights: The Golden State Warriors were again without Steph Curry, who is scheduled for a reevaluation on Sunday after going through his usual warmup routine on Saturday
Post-Match Reflections: The Golden State Warriors improved to 5-1 on the NBA season with their win over the Houston Rockets
Miscellaneous Highlights: The loss dropped Houston to an even 3-3 on the season, which has them tied with the San Antonio Spurs, Minnesota Timberwolves, New Orleans Pelicans, Denver Nuggets, and Sacramento Kings in the Western Conference standings
Others: Draymond Green should have fouled out with 1:26 remaining in the fourth quarter, but was ultimately disqualified with eight seconds remaining
